Multi-Domain Real-World Datasets
End-to-End Data Preprocessing Pipeline
 Overview

This project presents a comprehensive and modular data preprocessing pipeline designed to handle real-world datasets from multiple domains, specifically:

 E-commerce transaction data
 Healthcare stroke prediction data

The goal is to transform raw, messy data into clean, structured, and analysis-ready datasets through a robust and reusable pipeline.

 Key Features
 Data Quality Assessment
 Data Cleaning (missing values, duplicates, outliers)
 Data Transformation & Feature Engineering
 Dimensionality Reduction (PCA, Feature Selection)
 Discretization & Concept Hierarchies
 Modular and Reusable Pipeline Design
 Pipeline Architecture

The preprocessing framework is built using three main components:

DataCleaner → Handles missing values, outliers, duplicates
DataTransformer → Feature engineering, encoding, scaling
DataReducer → PCA, feature selection, sampling

These components are orchestrated into a flexible end-to-end pipeline.

 Datasets
1. E-Commerce Dataset
 ~541,000 transactions
 Multiple countries
 Issues: missing customer IDs, duplicates, invalid values
2. Stroke Prediction Dataset
 5,110 patient records
 Clinical & demographic features
 Issues: missing BMI, class imbalance
 Techniques Used
Missing value imputation (KNN, mode, sentinel values)
Outlier handling (IQR, winsorization)
Feature engineering (RFM, risk score)
Encoding (label, one-hot, frequency, ordinal)
Scaling (MinMax, Standard, Robust)
Dimensionality reduction:
PCA
SelectKBest
Random Forest importance
Discretization:
Equal-width / frequency
Entropy-based
K-means
Domain-based
 Results
 100% missing values handled
 Significant reduction in duplicates
 Improved data consistency and validity
 Dimensionality reduced while preserving >95% variance
 Enhanced interpretability through discretization and feature engineering
